Key Match Events: The Lakers trailed by 22 points in the second quarter but rallied to win 123-116.
The Lakers outscored Phoenix 35-24 in the third quarter to take the lead.
Miscellaneous Highlights: JJ Reddick is the first Los Angeles coach to win his first two games since Phil Jackson in 1999.
Others: Anthony Davis scored 35 points, Austin Reaves added 26, and LeBron James had 17 of his 21 points in the second half.
